## Semantic Verification Against Phase 13 Criteria

- `RunPostPrTestsExecutor` is the dedicated `run_post_pr_tests` executor and remains registered in the default registry.
- Command configuration is deterministic and argv-only. It accepts explicit `argv` or a `command_id` resolved through a configured command registry; shell-string-only `command`/`shell`, missing command arrays, empty argv, unrecognized command IDs, unsafe working directories, and malformed retry caps route to fatal/config artifacts where the binding is available.
- The production runner uses `std::process::Command` without a shell, passes args as argv, sets `stdin` null, captures stdout/stderr, enforces positive `timeout_seconds`, writes full stdout/stderr log artifacts, and stores bounded excerpts in `post-pr-test-result.json`.
- Binding validation is performed by reading `pr.json`, `pr-remediation-plan.json`, and `pr-remediation-result.json` through `PrFollowupArtifactStore`, which validates common binding/history metadata before consumption.
- `post-pr-test-result.json` records `test_state`, command status/argv/exit/log metadata, `verification_retry_index`, `max_verification_retries`, `retry_scope`, `plan_artifact_sequence`, `remediation_result_artifact_sequence`, and `verification_retry_exhausted`.
- Local verification success returns `StepOutcome::Success`; failed test commands return `Fixable` while artifact-backed retries remain; retry exhaustion and infrastructure/configuration failures return `Fatal`.
- The retry cap is artifact-backed from the prior bound `post-pr-test-result.json` for the same plan artifact sequence. The P13 test verifies retry indexes 0 and 1 are fixable, then index 2 with max 2 is fatal/exhausted.
- P13 shell-safety coverage verifies malicious remediation text is not interpolated into post-PR test argv and does not require P14 push executor behavior.
- P13 expected-failing manifest entries were removed and verifier passed with only later-phase P14/P15/P17 entries.
- Adjacent P13 markers with `@requirement` and exact `@pseudocode lines 29-33` are present for touched production/test items; marker audit passed.

